The paper deals with image steganography, which involves manipulating images to hide secret messages. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) to optimize the perceptual quality of the images produced, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the evasion of steganalysis tools, which falls under the cryptography (cs.CR) category.
